sentences: Piet Noordijk (May 25, 1932 – October 8, 2011) was a Dutch saxophonist.
He was awarded the Wessel Ilcken Prize in 1965.
Between 1978 and 1992, Noordijk played alto saxophone with the Metropole Orchestra.
In 1987 he won a Bird Award.
